Html:
Create a LoginWindow and modify the start up URI in App.xaml to point to the login window. Do the logic of authenticating the user and once successful, close the login window and create the main application window. Here is a snippet from an app I am working on which does exactly this:<br />
<div style="color:Black;background-color:White;"><pre>
<span style="color:Blue;">var</span> mainWindow = <span style="color:Blue;">new</span> MainWindow();
<span style="color:Blue;">var</span> loginWindow = Window.GetWindow(<span style="color:Blue;">this</span>);

mainWindow.Show();
<span style="color:Blue;">if</span> (loginWindow != <span style="color:Blue;">null</span>) loginWindow.Close();
</pre></div>
